The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 10 March is 40,656 (4,705.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 March, there were 321 new confirmed cases (37.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 26 February, there were 566 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 43% (245 fewer cases).
